<paragraph id="8BF136E8995D113CFF36FCA7FE61FC6B" blockId="92.[124,653,193,950]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">
ETYMOLOGY: The Latin specific epithet 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D6B995D113CFDC9FCA7FF50FC80" authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="improcerus">
<emphasis id="B93AEAFA995D113CFDC9FCA7FF50FC80" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">improcerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
means undersized. I selected the name because my initial impression of this specimen was that it was a small individual of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D6B995D113CFF30FC11FE7DFC6B" authority="(Chevrolat)" baseAuthorityName="Chevrolat" box="[159,462,926,950]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Clerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutellaris">
<emphasis id="B93AEAFA995D113CFF30FC11FE88FC68" box="[159,315,927,950]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">A. scutellaris</emphasis>
(Chevrolat)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
